At least 1.4 million Kenyans are staring at starvation following projections that parts of the country will experience drought in the coming weeks. Government spokesperson col. (RTD) Cyrus Oguna says that the counties of Turkana, Marsabit and Mandera may be greatly affected. a prediction by the Kenya meteorological department for the month of April shows that the affected areas will experience serious rain shortage that will threaten lives and livelihoods. ibrahim karanja reports.